sense.name: come/go before in time or space
sense.examples: She preceded him into the room. What day precedes the Day of Atonement? Your reputation precedes you. Every goal is preceded by a dream. In 1920s real estate collapse and stagflation preceded the stock market crash. What preceded the blackboard? His wife and son preceded him in death.

sense.name: preface
sense.commentary: Syntax Is: NP1[agent] PRECEDE NP2[cotheme] PP{with NP[cotheme]}
sense.examples: She always precedes her lectures with a joke. Mr. Simmons has preceded friendly offers with a hostile tender offer.
